<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2945> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2945" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Niccolini (FTP 130f.) wishes to relate lines 115-116 in Liv. Oxy. Per. 50 (M. Sca[n]tius [...]am tulit in stupro deprehensi[...]) with the passage of the Lex Scantinia concerning sexual perversion. The name however appears to be Scantius, the office is uncertain, and no clear connection can be made with the law (see RE s. v. \"Lex Scantinia\")." .
